  "text": "One method developed in this laboratory for isolating and identifying the tumour-related light Correspondence: F.K. Stevenson Received 12 December 1982; accepted 19 February 1983. chain has been described [CITATION_1] Tables  I and II. Most patients with CLL appeared to have  a B cell neoplasm by the demonstration of one light  chain type at the cell surface by immunofluorescence. The 2 patients with no detectable surface Ig showed monotypic light chain export in vitro when culture fluids were analyzed by radioimmunoassay thus demonstrating their B cell nature.",
